Intro to App Building with Salesforce [DENVER]





July 22, 20179:00am - 4:30pm    

RSVP




Interested in an in-demand career with salaries up to six-figures? The job market for Salesforce professionals is growing, with over 300,000 job openings for Salesforce skills created last year*. In this class, you'll get a crash course in building simple employee-facing business apps that run on both a web browser and a mobile device - without writing any code! This is not a sales pitch. I’m a Salesforce professional, and I’m passionate about bringing diversity to the tech sector and helping women learn about powerful career options. Whether you’re familiar with Salesforce from your work experience or are just looking for a career in a hot field, join us to learn about app-building on Salesforce. This class runs for 9am to 4:30pm with 30 minutes for lunch, and time for lots of breaks!  WHAT YOU WILL LEAVE THIS CLASS WITH:What is Salesforce and what are the career opportunities for Salesforce Admins and Developers?App-building concepts including data modeling, user interfaces, business logic, reports, dashboards, and mobile.Hands-on and guided project building to build a sample app in one day.Introduction to Trailhead, a fun online learning platform for Salesforce.Resources for connecting with the Salesforce community. PREPARING YOURSELF FOR THIS WORKSHOP:• Trailhead, the fun free way to learn Salesforce• Salesforce1 Mobile App (AppStore and Google Play)• Students should be fairly familiar with using web and mobile applications and Googling for answers to all of life’s questions. You do not need any prior Salesforce experience. TECHNOLOGY REQUIREMENTS:Please bring a laptop, not an iPad/tablet. The visual development tools only run on a modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari 9.x and 10.x on Mac OS X, Internet Explorer 11). LOCATION:Turing School of Software & Design[masked]th St. Suite 100Denver, CO  TRANSIT OPTIONS:Take the H, F or D light rail lines to the 18th & California stop.Take the free 16th Street Mall Ride or the Free MetroRide to the California Street stop.  HOSTED BY:   QUESTIONS?   We're here to help! If you have additional questions or would like to talk further before signing up for an event, please contact Cara Jo Miller or Bree Thomas at [masked] WHY CHARGE?   We charge a fair registration fee for workshops/classes for a few reasons. A portion of the fee goes to the instructor to thank them for volunteering their time. The rest of the fee goes back to the community to pay for scholarship and food/drink for this and future events. QUESTIONS? We're here to help! If you have additional questions or would like to talk further before signing up for an event, please contact Cara Jo Miller at [masked] SCHOLARSHIPS We are offering scholarships on a limited basis for students with financial need. Please complete our scholarship application [http://gdiboulder.com...] if you are interested.  https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/U6i64sTAxuZWsApHATh5Vg-2TM9e5mYJHQ6chQpXNY7J6UeZMg8wYEX8EIg1wyQvhd6758fxcKi-SSePymdsubE_v945fNOaIL-Iq1EENHOHr2u6QVwVMLmcWvZJMn0NFBoqUhqy Get to know the GDI Boulder/Denver community — join us on Slack! Before RSVPing to this event, please make sure you have read and understand the Class Polices. 

